Reuse of existing softwares/patches:

BSD Router Project is based upon/includes various free software packages, listed below. The authors of BSDRP would like to thank the authors of these software packages for their efforts.

* FreeBSD:  Copyright (c) 1995-2009 The FreeBSD Project. All rights reserved.
* Gitoyen-NanoBSD-Quagga-router : patch to NanoBSD that add ports compiling support.
* Quagga routing software.
* The BIRD Internet Routing Daemon 
* Net-SNMP 
* Idea of using glabel for disk type absraction: Scott Ullrich (pfSense)
* "show memory" is a shell port of the perl freebsd-memory script: Copyright (c) 2003-2004 Ralf S. Engelschall
* FreeVRRPd : VRRP daemon
* uCARP: userland CARP daemon
* fprobe: Slava Astashonok
* OpenLLDP: Terry Simons and Jason Peterson 
* DHCP server and relay: Internet Systems Consortium
* ssmtp: extremely simple MTA to get mail off the system to a mail hub
